post_text:
7th and 8th grade Individuals & Societies students participated in a research Summative, generating questions that would help them better understand the Battle of New Orleans, the War of 1812, and daily life in 1815. They identified likely sources of information, and attended a re-enactment where they observed demonstrations and questioned the performers. Students then reflected on the research process, their teamwork skills and the knowledge that they gained.

Mr. Schroeder writes, "Everyone had a great time and represented Morris Jeff very well. Immense thanks to the National Park Services for hosting us, and their commitment to preserving history and sharing it with our community."

@nationalparkservice #proudtobeIB @ Chalmette Battlefield

